timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 9' Great work from Ramos there, but Higuita's thru-ball can't quite find Ribeiro . Orlando City with the better of it so far. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: 10' 0-0: Scrappy start here. Kaka with a nice move along the touchline, but nothing particularly incisive yet. #ORLvDC #MLSonFOX #MLS

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: Orlando sharpening up now. #DCU will have to keep connecting passes & keep reading OCSC passes ahead of time.

timelineItems.name: Richard
timelineItems.text: Constantly impressed by the crowds #OCSC draw.

timelineItems.name: Tim Donahoe
timelineItems.text: #ORLvDC Can't see Espindola or Arrieta going 90 in the mid June central Florida heat and humidity today,

timelineItems.name: Jeff Gardner
timelineItems.text: Network support at the Citrus Bowl for the @OrlandoCitySC @dcunited @MLS match #ORLvDC #DefyExpectations http://t.co/gIXDHErnBC

timelineItems.name: Thomas Floyd
timelineItems.text: #DCU seems unable to solve Orlando's pressure and find Espindola or Arrieta with any regularity. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Looks like a 4-4-2 for Orlando City to start the match. Kaká playing slightly deeper than Ribeiro up top. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: As expected, the Orlando lineup graphic had Avila & Neal listed in the opposite spots. Avila at RW, Neal in central midfield. #DCU

timelineItems.desc: Two teams now suddenly in the thick of the Eastern Conference chase for positions meet for a third time this season when Orlando City SC play host to D.C. United on Sunday evening at the Citrus Bowl before a FOX Sports 1 audience.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: Orlando City SC vs DC United | June 14, 2015

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: 20' 0-0: Orlando City with plenty of the ball. Nothing through the lines yet, though. United well organized. #ORLvDC #MLSonFOX #MLS

timelineItems.name: Andrew Martonik
timelineItems.text: Not sure Shea has a good idea of what position he's playing today. All over the field. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 22' 0-0 halfway through the first half. Orlando City with better possession, but neither team with any dangerous chances yet. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Ben Bromley
timelineItems.text: apparently it is questionable facial hair all across #DCU's midfield

timelineItems.name: American Soccer 24/7
timelineItems.text: Best shot on goal we've seen all night. Kaka blast one at hamid in the 23' #ORLvDC #MLS

timelineItems.name: Thomas Floyd
timelineItems.text: Classic #DCU on the road — absorbing plenty of pressure, then putting together the best chance of the half.

timelineItems.desc: Penalty conceded by Taylor Kemp (D.C. United) after a foul in the penalty area.
timelineItems.title: PENALTY: Pedro Ribeiro has a shot saved then draws a PK

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Lewis Neal with a beautiful pass to Ribeiro but he cant quite get to it. Match is starting to heat up now #ORLvDC

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  Orlando City SC 1, D.C. United 0. Kaka(Orlando City SC) header from the center of the box to the center of the goal following a penalty kick
timelineItems.title: PK GOAL: Kaka heads in his penalty rebound for the opener

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Rivero has made a right mess of that sequence, hasn't he? #ORLvDC #MLS

timelineItems.name: Christian Bruey
timelineItems.text: Boden giving too much room on the outside nearly leads to an early goal for @dcunited #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Joe Tansey
timelineItems.text: I can see why that's a penalty, but I can also see why it isn't. Ribeiro is a big dude and he went down really easy. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Thomas Floyd
timelineItems.text: Poor from Kemp — don't go into a challenge with that much aggression when the opponent has his back to goal in a harmless spot. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Inside MLS
timelineItems.text: 30' ORL 1-0: Break out the oranges. It's a hydration break. #ORLvDC #MLS #MLSonFOX

timelineItems.text: Kaka scored the first goal! #OCSC http://t.co/iGYgIOatID

timelineItems.name: #BazTastic
timelineItems.text: Kaká PK!! #ORLvDC http://t.co/cnZ7bbzO8G

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: Another hard foul from Arrieta. Think he's still bitter we let him go after 12 hours or so...? #OCSC

timelineItems.text: Let's go Lions! Time for @OrlandoCitySC revenge. #ORLvDC http://t.co/aMDXAgQpG2

timelineItems.text: I am wearing a headband, though not my Rolfe headband, alas. #DCU -L http://t.co/38PggnkgY8

timelineItems.text: Knocking another #MLS venue off my to-visit list tonight. #ORLvDC http://t.co/msfHFpX8M5

timelineItems.name: RAG
timelineItems.text: At the Citrus Bowl. GO CITY!!! #ManTheWall #ORLvDC http://t.co/QTGE0sHHbN

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: #DCU has not come out of the water break well.

timelineItems.name: Nick Leyva
timelineItems.text: The captain strikes again!! #ORLvDC http://t.co/rqFM5cGp22

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Lair of the Lions. #ORLvDC kicks off now on @FOXSports1. #SoccerSunday http://t.co/BshbIT1hb4

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: Darwin Ceren has been an under-appreciated force for Orlando City this year & Larin has been hot. City will miss both tonight. #MLS #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Joe Tansey
timelineItems.text: Ribeiro vs. Birnbaum & Boswell should be fun to watch. Kaka vs. Arnaud & Kitchen obviously a big one too. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: VenessTravelMedia
timelineItems.text: It's still 90F as we approach #ORLvDC kickoff here at the @CitrusBowl. Who is likely to wilt in the heat if it's a close game...?

timelineItems.name: VenessTravelMedia
timelineItems.text: Without Larin, Paterson & Rochez, @OrlandoCitySC have no goalscoring potential on bench tonite. Starting XI must be on their game. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 38' Nice run by Ramos, good cross as well, but it's JUST out of the reach of Ribeiro. Orlando City still on the gas. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Inchy Tifo unveiled by the wall. #ORLvDC http://t.co/gee8BoYFNK

timelineItems.name: D.C. United
timelineItems.text: The starters salute the traveling #DCU fans - in their sun-baked section - and we're about to get underway! #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Orlando City are gonna miss Darwin Ceren's presence in the defensive midfield vs DC. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Collin and Espindola is that rare matchup between two players who have never, ever committed a foul. #ORLvDC #MLS

timelineItems.name: Chris Webb
timelineItems.text: Rolfe has been invisible for the past two games. Better as a forward for this group #DCU #unitedmania

timelineItems.name: Gustavo Araujo
timelineItems.text: Heath is surely experimenting today as Shea is being played through the middle, which is weird as hell. #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Walter Pacheco
timelineItems.text: Awesome view from Wells Fargo suite! Go @OrlandoCitySC #ORLvDC http://t.co/qcpYgdWcJk

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: That said, Orlando was the better team & given how the previous #DCU visit went, probably a fair scoreline. DC not bad, but not good either.

timelineItems.name: Orlando City SC
timelineItems.text: Locked in. #ORLvDC http://t.co/i03R2ckWJn

timelineItems.name: Gracie Weiss
timelineItems.text: #ORLvDC Goooaallll! http://t.co/kIyUiINfHa

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: Orlando defense has looked pretty beatable even as most #DCU attacks involve jut 2-3 players. One more runner & chances will come.

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Ribeiro with a headed chance, just over the bar, Hamid seemed to have it covered though. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Neil W. Blackmon
timelineItems.text: Battle between Espindola and Collin tonight in the heat has been splendid stuff. From the ref politicking to the football. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Ben Bromley
timelineItems.text: Brek Shea was not hauled down, he left his arm in to try and gain an advantage #dcu #mls

timelineItems.name: Steven Clark
timelineItems.text: I will be happy to see #DCU continue to win balls in the midfield. I'll be happier when they get the ball in the opposition half.

timelineItems.name: Jeff Krause
timelineItems.text: The speed of that #OCSC counterattack was slower than a U11 rec league team. #OCSCvDCU

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: #DCU was horribly unprepared for that short CK. Avila should have done much better.

timelineItems.name: Mickey wants his say
timelineItems.text: For me, Avila has underperformed up to this point. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: Shea with a chance in the box but his first touch lets him down and it goes out for a goal kick #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Christian Bruey
timelineItems.text: As was the case back in April, @OrlandoCitySC taking the game to @dcunited. Can they find a second goal? #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: DC building up the pressure which will leave them vulnerable in the back. #OCSC needs another goal to kill the game. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Ben Bromley
timelineItems.text: Ribeiro seems like a delightful person #dcu #mls

timelineItems.title: CHANCE: Fabian Espindola takes a look but fires wide

timelineItems.name: Orlando City SC
timelineItems.text: 60' Let us nominate Cristian Higuita for Man of the Match. Just dominating the midfield out there tonight. http://t.co/E7dbkj0xis #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Bob
timelineItems.text: Two give aways when in on goal. Classic DeLeon #Dcu

timelineItems.name: Gavin Ewbank
timelineItems.text: #OCSC's living dangerously in this second half. Too many turnovers, luckily DC hasn't been able to capitalize.

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: #DCU having their best 6-7 minute spell of the game. Still not creating enough in the middle, but Aguilar might be able to change that.

timelineItems.name: Greg_YNWA1
timelineItems.text: #DCU has done enough lately that thru 63' its been a 50-50 game. Not playing that poorly. Kemp's clumsy foul the difference in 1-0 scoreline

timelineItems.name: Ben Bromley
timelineItems.text: So D.C. United has looked much more calm and composed in the second half. But I thought Ben Olsen couldn't do that to his teams #dcu #mls

timelineItems.name: Matt Fischer
timelineItems.text: Not often Kaka has missed an open runner during his career. Missed Brek there. #OCSC

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: #DCU forcing some rather awkward/rushed clearances from Collin & St. Ledger. Inching closer, but inches might not do it.

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: Much better start this time around for #DCU. Anticipating Orlando passes, getting angles right. Looking like a smart team.

timelineItems.name: The Mane Land
timelineItems.text: 6' Good passing from Orlando, but it's off Higuita for a goal kick in the end. Shea and Avila are VERY narrow in this formation. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Jan Schulte-Wittreck
timelineItems.text: What a great atmosphere in Orlando! #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Scott Wyant
timelineItems.text: Have to love the pace Aguilar is bringing right now. He's big a difference maker since coming on. #DCU

timelineItems.name: Adam
timelineItems.text: Saint Ledger is having a rough game. Taking a lot of punishment from guys he outweighs by 30lbs... #DCU #orlandocity

timelineItems.name: Jordan Allan
timelineItems.text: Birnbaum with some real poor clearances tonight. Weak ball that led to the terrible PK call and sending a ball out for a corner #DCU #ORLvDC

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Chris Korb (D.C. United) left footed shot from outside the box is saved in the center of the goal.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Chris Korb fires an effort from distance

timelineItems.name: Greg_YNWA1
timelineItems.text: Maybe not #DCU worst performance of the season, but could be the most frustrating one.

timelineItems.name: Alex
timelineItems.text: These guys are warriors no denying it. Putting it all on the field. Things to work on but Im proud of this team #ORLvDC #MLS @OrlandoCitySC

timelineItems.name: DC United WUFC
timelineItems.text: Picture taking at night is easier. Vamos!! #DCU -L http://t.co/esMpHlh6NL

timelineItems.name: City Soccer Talk
timelineItems.text: DC clearly wants to keep play in the middle of the field. Begging #OCSC to play it wide. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: With all 3 subs used, #DCU's last gamble could theoretically be a back 3 (meaning Kemp to LM, Doyle up front). We'll see.

timelineItems.name: Kristen Fitz
timelineItems.text: Orlando is working hard to park that bus. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Kirby
timelineItems.text: Adrian Heath needs to think about using his subs. Some of them out on their feet. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Greg_YNWA1
timelineItems.text: Lot of tired legs for #DCU. Seems the black and red are out of gas. Lot of walking and jogging. Hands on knees

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: Dangerous sub here. Rivas has great speed, #DCU pushing plenty of numbers up & stretching width as well.

timelineItems.name: NathanK
timelineItems.text: Looks like Doyle is trying out Rolfe's magic headband #DCU

timelineItems.name: Christopher Hunter
timelineItems.text: DC seem scared to bring the house though they could. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: As soon as Rivas had an inch of daylight I said out loud "this shot's going into row 20." Dude is 100% reliable. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Andy Winner ï¸
timelineItems.text: I see Sean Franklin hasn't recovered from getting his ankles broken by Giovinco last weekend #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: Why cross it to the guy making an awesome run to the back post when you can take a tight-angle shot with like 2% chance of scoring? #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Kyle McCarthy
timelineItems.text: Heath continues to play with fire on these Kaka substitutions. #ORLvDC #MLSonFOX #MLS

timelineItems.name: Ryan Brister
timelineItems.text: Orlando has killed this game brilliantly. #ORLvDC

timelineItems.name: Christian Bruey
timelineItems.text: Arnaud is lucky he didn't get a second yellow after that tackle on @BrekShea #ORLvDC

timelineItems.text: FINAL: @OrlandoCitySC defeat Eastern Conference leaders D.C. United 1-0 to improve unbeaten streak to five. #ORLvDC http://t.co/KtW8qVoRnc
